I'll remember that. Although...

239
00:13:21,718 --> 00:13:23,219
[TILARNA] ...do you
honestly expect this guy

240
00:13:23,261 --> 00:13:25,179
to tell us who's behind it?

241
00:13:25,221 --> 00:13:29,851
[KEI] Hey, you got any
last words? We'll listen.

242
00:13:29,892 --> 00:13:31,477
<i>Leeze.</i>

243
00:13:31,519 --> 00:13:33,479
‐‐[TILARNA gasps]
‐‐[KEI] Huh?

244
00:13:33,521 --> 00:13:35,106
I thank you.

245
00:13:37,900 --> 00:13:42,071
What the hell? His face is‐‐

246
00:13:42,113 --> 00:13:43,448
[TILARNA]
<i>Mildina zarhf.</i>

247
00:13:43,489 --> 00:13:44,782
[KEI]
What's that mean?

248
00:13:44,824 --> 00:13:46,451
[TILARNA]
Transformation magic.

249
00:13:46,492 --> 00:13:48,786
It seems to have worn off
partway through.

250
00:13:48,828 --> 00:13:51,247
I noticed that at some
point in the pursuit.

251
00:13:51,289 --> 00:13:53,374
[KEI]
Wait, this guy's an Earthling!

252
00:13:53,416 --> 00:13:55,710
[TILARNA]
I know. And he's a warrior.

253
00:13:55,752 --> 00:13:58,004
He was using mildey
all by himself.

254
00:13:58,046 --> 00:14:00,006
No one controlled him
as he fought me.

255
00:14:00,048 --> 00:14:01,966
Zelada's puppets
couldn't do that.

256
00:14:02,008 --> 00:14:05,094
This man was something
I haven't encountered. Ever.

257
00:14:05,136 --> 00:14:07,847
I thought humans
couldn't use magic.

258
00:14:07,889 --> 00:14:11,976
You remember Elbaji? He had no
trouble with human science.

259
00:14:12,018 --> 00:14:14,729
I think Earthlings can
plausibly do the reverse.

260
00:14:14,771 --> 00:14:15,772
Perfect.

261
00:14:20,568 --> 00:14:23,738
[TILARNA] Let me see that.
It smells strongly of latena.

262
00:14:23,780 --> 00:14:27,700
[KEI] Hm? Okay, just don't
touch the trigger.

263
00:14:29,285 --> 00:14:31,412
[TILARNA]
Take out the bullets first.

264
00:14:31,454 --> 00:14:33,247
[KEI] This thing
is evidence, you know.

265
00:14:33,289 --> 00:14:35,291
Don't tell anyone we did this.

266
00:14:35,333 --> 00:14:40,296
[TILARNA speaks Farbani]

267
00:14:41,714 --> 00:14:45,051
[KEI gasps]
What do you think you're doing?

268
00:14:48,596 --> 00:14:51,349
Man, I told you
that was evidence!

269
00:14:51,391 --> 00:14:52,934
[TILARNA]
It's Vaifaht steel.

270
00:14:52,975 --> 00:14:54,435
What's that mean?

271
00:14:56,270 --> 00:15:00,775
[speaks Farbani]

272
00:15:02,735 --> 00:15:04,570
[KEI]
The gunpowder, too?

273
00:15:04,612 --> 00:15:07,990
[TILARNA] How dare they.
Vaifaht steel is sacred.

274
00:15:08,032 --> 00:15:10,785
It shouldn't be used
for such awful things.

275
00:15:12,412 --> 00:15:14,664
[KEI] So, that's how this
guy smuggled a gun past

276
00:15:14,705 --> 00:15:18,376
the security checkpoint.
You clever bastard.

277
00:15:18,418 --> 00:15:20,586
[TILARNA] His methods
were beyond masterful.

278
00:15:20,628 --> 00:15:22,755
The greatest vaifaht
blacksmiths in my country

279
00:15:22,797 --> 00:15:25,883
couldn't make this.
A human? Unheard of.

280
00:15:25,925 --> 00:15:27,635
[KEI]
All right, change it back.

281
00:15:27,677 --> 00:15:28,845
[TILARNA]
But...

282
00:15:28,886 --> 00:15:31,681
[KEI] Just do it. You can
play with it again later.

283
00:15:33,057 --> 00:15:34,517
[TILARNA]
Oh, fine.

284
00:15:35,768 --> 00:15:40,815
[speaks Farbani]

285
00:15:42,316 --> 00:15:44,485
Something else I
should mention.

286
00:15:44,527 --> 00:15:47,113
The last word he said
before he died, <i>Leeze</i>‐‐

287
00:15:47,155 --> 00:15:49,115
[MALE FBI AGENT A]
Hold it right there!

288
00:15:49,157 --> 00:15:50,825
[CHAN]
This the FBI.

289
00:15:52,201 --> 00:15:53,786
Whoa, bossy.

290
00:15:53,828 --> 00:15:56,998
Is that how they teach you
feds to treat a fellow cop?

291
00:16:02,712 --> 00:16:05,673
I don't consider ineffectual
morons who murder their suspects

292
00:16:05,715 --> 00:16:07,592
fellow cops, buddy.

293
00:16:07,633 --> 00:16:09,177
[KEI]
Hey, what are you doing?

294
00:16:09,218 --> 00:16:12,346
[CHAN] None of your business.
This case is our jurisdiction.

295
00:16:12,388 --> 00:16:16,642
So, take your city cop ass home,
if you'd be so kind.

296
00:16:17,935 --> 00:16:19,604
[KEI grunts]

297
00:16:19,645 --> 00:16:24,650
[police sirens]

298
00:16:27,111 --> 00:16:29,071
Took you jokers long enough.

299
00:16:38,706 --> 00:16:42,418
You kept your mouth shut
like I told you to, right?

300
00:16:42,460 --> 00:16:44,837
[TILARNA]
Kei. I'm tired of saying it.

301
00:16:44,879 --> 00:16:47,131
Isn't there something you
need to tell me first?

302
00:16:47,173 --> 00:16:49,634
[KEI chuckles] When you're
mad your face looks funny.

303
00:16:49,675 --> 00:16:52,136
I am mad, aren't you?

304
00:16:52,178 --> 00:16:54,305
[KEI] Nah, just regretting
my choices.

305
00:16:54,347 --> 00:16:56,807
When Coal got shot I should
have pretended to be deaf

306
00:16:56,849 --> 00:16:58,601
and gone out for
a nice big steak.

307
00:16:58,643 --> 00:17:02,563
[TILARNA] Tsk! You're pathetic.
Unworthy of upholding justice!

308
00:17:02,605 --> 00:17:04,065
[ZIMMER]
Quit your bickering you two.

309
00:17:04,106 --> 00:17:08,444
I want a report from both of
you jerks by 19:00 tomorrow.

310
00:17:08,486 --> 00:17:09,654
[KEI]
Yeah, and then what?

311
00:17:09,695 --> 00:17:11,739
Are you gonna take us off
the case or something?

312
00:17:11,781 --> 00:17:13,658
[ZIMMER]
Oh, you wish, don'tcha?

313
00:17:13,699 --> 00:17:16,244
We're gonna solve
this one as a team.

314
00:17:16,285 --> 00:17:18,162
They may have made
off with the body,

315
00:17:18,204 --> 00:17:20,289
but we have the photo you
took of the guy's face.

316
00:17:20,331 --> 00:17:22,542
Not a great clue,
but it's something.

317
00:17:22,583 --> 00:17:24,252
I did good police work, huh?

318
00:17:24,293 --> 00:17:25,795
Don't be a dumbass, Kei.

319
00:17:25,836 --> 00:17:28,089
If you'd done a better job
cornering the suspect,

320
00:17:28,130 --> 00:17:29,674
we might have gotten
more out of him.

321
00:17:29,715 --> 00:17:30,758
Well, you're not wrong.

322
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:33,970
But, Chief! That wasn't
a possibility here!

323
00:17:34,011 --> 00:17:35,846
Our opponent was
a skilled warrior

324
00:17:35,888 --> 00:17:40,017
who could even use mildey!
We stopped him from escaping!

325
00:17:40,059 --> 00:17:43,729
Yeah, yeah... Ugh.

326
00:17:43,771 --> 00:17:46,107
Coal Mozeleemay is dead.

327
00:17:46,148 --> 00:17:47,858
The Paramedics were
able to transport him

328
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:50,736
to Patterson Hospital,
but he died there.

329
00:17:50,778 --> 00:17:52,947
[KEI]
What a nightmare.

330
00:17:52,989 --> 00:17:54,073
[ZIMMER]
The commissioner's getting ready

331
00:17:54,115 --> 00:17:55,866
to give a press conference.

332
00:17:55,908 --> 00:17:59,453
If you're curious, you can
ask your ex about it later.

333
00:17:59,495 --> 00:18:01,497
She's probably surrounded
by a bunch of VIPs,

334
00:18:01,539 --> 00:18:04,584
telling them the size of
the guy's ass again.

335
00:18:04,625 --> 00:18:06,961
[KEI]
Sounds fun, but no.

336
00:18:07,003 --> 00:18:08,838
C'mon, Tilarna,
back to the station.

337
00:18:08,879 --> 00:18:09,422
[TILARNA]
Right.

338
00:18:09,463 --> 00:18:10,423
[ZIMMER]
Matoba!

339
00:18:10,464 --> 00:18:11,924
Yeah, what is it?

340
00:18:11,966 --> 00:18:14,093
You sure your ass ain't
hiding something?

341
00:18:16,596 --> 00:18:20,808
Man, you're good.
Yeah, we are, actually.

342
00:18:20,850 --> 00:18:21,809
[ZIMMER]
Well?

343
00:18:21,851 --> 00:18:25,104
Listen. I can't tell you here.

344
00:18:25,146 --> 00:18:27,648
Let's talk about it
back at the office.

345
00:18:30,484 --> 00:18:32,361
It's rather difficult
to explain.

346
00:18:32,403 --> 00:18:35,364
Earthlings have trouble with
the concept of vaifaht steel.

347
00:18:35,406 --> 00:18:37,867
The closest thing you have in
your world is the material

348
00:18:37,908 --> 00:18:41,037
you just explained to me:
the shape‐memory alloys.

349
00:18:41,078 --> 00:18:44,457
However, vaifaht steel changes
in response to latena,

350
00:18:44,498 --> 00:18:45,875
rather than temperature.

351
00:18:45,916 --> 00:18:48,836
[ZIMMER] So, it's like a
magic metal? Ridiculous!

352
00:18:48,878 --> 00:18:50,713
This whole thing's ridiculous!

353
00:18:50,755 --> 00:18:52,214
Hey, calm your tits.

354
00:18:52,256 --> 00:18:52,923
[ZIMMER grumbles]

355
00:18:52,965 --> 00:18:56,260
[TILARNA] Vaifaht steel is
extracted from certain trees,

356
00:18:56,302 --> 00:18:59,347
and its raw form has a
texture similar to cotton.

357
00:18:59,388 --> 00:19:02,683
From that, it's processed
into thin, strong fibers.

358
00:19:02,725 --> 00:19:05,686
[TONY] I get it. Then you
weave it, like cloth.

359
00:19:05,728 --> 00:19:06,812
[TILARNA]
Correct.

360
00:19:06,854 --> 00:19:09,482
It's woven into cloth
with a special loom.

361
00:19:09,523 --> 00:19:10,107
At this point,

362
00:19:10,149 --> 00:19:13,027
the final shape of the item
you're making is decided.

363
00:19:13,069 --> 00:19:15,529
Occasionally,
it's made into art,

364
00:19:15,571 --> 00:19:17,615
but most of the time,
it's weapons.

365
00:19:19,241 --> 00:19:21,702
[speaks Farbani]

366
00:19:26,957 --> 00:19:28,793
[ALL gasp]

367
00:19:28,834 --> 00:19:31,504
[JAMIE] So, um, the mass
of the object itself

368
00:19:31,545 --> 00:19:33,130
doesn't really change?

369
00:19:33,172 --> 00:19:38,886
[speaks Farbani]

370
00:19:38,928 --> 00:19:40,763
[TILARNA]
As my fellow coworkers,

371
00:19:40,805 --> 00:19:43,015
you get the special
privilege of touching it.

372
00:19:43,057 --> 00:19:43,849
‐‐[TONY] Oh?
‐‐[JAMIE] Huh?

373
00:19:43,891 --> 00:19:44,725
[CAMMY]
Huh?

374
00:19:44,767 --> 00:19:45,851
[ZIMMER growls]

375
00:19:45,893 --> 00:19:47,687
[TONY]
Heavy!

376
00:19:47,728 --> 00:19:49,730
[TILARNA] All vaifaht steel
weapons are woven by

377
00:19:49,772 --> 00:19:52,441
specially trained
Lahge craftsmen.

378
00:19:52,483 --> 00:19:55,152
No two weapons in the
universe are alike.

379
00:19:55,194 --> 00:19:57,697
[JAMIE grunts] I'm amazed
your shoulders don't get all

380
00:19:57,738 --> 00:19:59,573
knotted up, wearing this
all the time.

381
00:19:59,615 --> 00:20:01,951
[TILARNA] Well, I do train
on a daily basis.

382
00:20:01,992 --> 00:20:03,619
That explains why
you're so short.

383
00:20:03,661 --> 00:20:05,037
That thing stunted your growth.

384
00:20:05,079 --> 00:20:06,247
[TILARNA grunts]

385
00:20:06,288 --> 00:20:07,957
[TONY]
Just to make sure I understand.

386
00:20:07,998 --> 00:20:10,835
You're saying vaifaht steel
items, weapons and other things,

387
00:20:10,876 --> 00:20:13,003
are extremely difficult to make.

388
00:20:13,045 --> 00:20:14,296
[TILARNA]
Correct.

389
00:20:14,338 --> 00:20:17,091
Creating something with
precision parts, like a gun,

390
00:20:17,133 --> 00:20:19,719
for example,
would be impossible,

391
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:22,012
even for a Lahge craftsman.

392
00:20:22,054 --> 00:20:24,181
Now you know why
this is so strange.

393
00:20:24,223 --> 00:20:26,517
[JAMIE] So, do you think
that gun is maybe a hybrid

394
00:20:26,559 --> 00:20:29,395
of Earth and Semanian
technology, then?

395
00:20:29,437 --> 00:20:32,732
Could it be possible that one of
these Lahge guys is working

396
00:20:32,773 --> 00:20:34,692
with someone from Earth?

397
00:20:36,527 --> 00:20:39,447
I guess... Possibly.

398
00:20:39,488 --> 00:20:43,325
I don't quite see how a Semanian
could make a weapon like that.

399
00:20:43,367 --> 00:20:47,079
Not without the help of someone
well‐versed in your technology.

400
00:20:47,121 --> 00:20:48,414
[clap]

401
00:20:48,456 --> 00:20:51,709
[ZIMMER] Okay, we know what
the next step is, then.

402
00:20:51,751 --> 00:20:55,755
Get to work investigating.
Dismissed. Get lost.

403
00:20:55,796 --> 00:20:57,798
Hold on, Matoba.

404
00:20:57,840 --> 00:20:59,216
[KEI]
Yeah, what?

405
00:20:59,258 --> 00:21:01,051
I want you to pay Tourte
a visit tomorrow

406
00:21:01,093 --> 00:21:02,470
and ask some questions.

407
00:21:02,511 --> 00:21:05,473
I secured permission from his
people for an interview.

408
00:21:10,978 --> 00:21:14,523
[KEI yawns]

409
00:21:14,565 --> 00:21:16,901
[TILARNA]
What do you want me to say?

410
00:21:16,942 --> 00:21:20,571
I don't know! I don't! I‐‐

411
00:21:20,613 --> 00:21:22,072
I'm hanging up.

412
00:21:22,114 --> 00:21:23,741
Damn, who was that?

413
00:21:23,783 --> 00:21:26,076
[TILARNA] An officer
from precinct 14.

414
00:21:26,118 --> 00:21:28,037
They got a complaint from the
owner of the three‐wheeler

415
00:21:28,078 --> 00:21:29,205
you commandeered.

416
00:21:29,246 --> 00:21:30,414
[KEI gasps]

417
00:21:30,456 --> 00:21:33,167
[TILARNA] They said he was
furious about the whole thing.

418
00:21:33,209 --> 00:21:33,918
What should we do?

419
00:21:33,959 --> 00:21:36,462
[KEI]
Hm. Yeah let's just ignore that.

420
00:21:38,255 --> 00:21:42,218
[PROTESTORS]
Go home! Go home! E. T. go home!

421
00:21:42,259 --> 00:21:46,305
Go home! Go home! E. T. go home!
Go home! Go home! E. T. go home!

422
00:21:46,347 --> 00:21:52,394
Go home! Go home!
E. T. go home...!

423
00:21:52,436 --> 00:21:54,021
[TILARNA exhales]

424
00:21:57,024 --> 00:22:01,028
[KEI sighs] I don't want
any trouble, okay?

425
00:22:01,070 --> 00:22:03,113
Ignore that, too.

426
00:22:03,155 --> 00:22:04,949
[TILARNA]
Yeah, I know.

427
00:22:04,990 --> 00:22:09,995
[CROWD chanting continues]

428
00:23:49,803 --> 00:23:52,056
[KEI]
Next time, on <i>Cop Craft</i>.

